The paper deals with the Fourier Entropy/Influence conjecture, which is a problem in computational complexity theory related to Boolean functions. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of Fourier coefficients and their concentration, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of lexicographic functions and their properties suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
